<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths end with a quantified worksheet plus one explicit trade-off sentence. The path is about how hard you stress-test the trade-off.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I have quantified my plan across at least four objectives and named, in one clear sentence, what I sacrificed to gain what I gained.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Worksheet plus trade-off sentence (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Quantify your plan across at least four of the seven objectives using the worksheet. Then write one explicit trade-off sentence: to get X (with a number), this plan gives up Y (with a number). The sentence has to let a reader see the cost, not just the win.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Re-optimize to trade a different objective (stretch)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Make a second version of your plan that protects the objective you sacrificed in version one, and see what that protection costs somewhere else. Compare the two. Being able to say "I could buy back flood resilience, but only by housing 4,000 fewer people" is exactly the reasoning a planning audience trusts.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Stress-test with a partner AI (choice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Take your trade-off sentence to whichever <a href="/ai-partners/equity-resilience-partner/">AI partner</a> is most likely to attack it. If you sacrificed green-blue space, let the Equity &amp; Resilience Partner press you; if you limited housing, let the Urban Planner. Revise the sentence so it survives the challenge. Document the exchange.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Peer-help — quantifying an objective (practice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If putting a number on an objective feels impossible, come to the peer-help table. Work one objective (say 15-minute access, as a rough percentage of homes within range) all the way to a number with a partner and Mr. Ignash, then repeat the method for the rest.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

